narrative: In 1999,  Jonathan Drew the founder of Acid Cigars pioneered the little known technique of infusing aromas into cigar tobacco. The result of the Blue Labeled line of acid cigars became an “acquired taste” that grew into one of the country’s biggest sellers. the Blondie and Kuba Kuba became must have products in every cigar store. Their taste is totally unique and brought in a whole new group of smokers. As time passed, many cigar Aficionado “purists” came to enjoy this blend as a pleasant break from traditional smokes.

What can you say about Arturo Fuente Cigars? They truly make a style for every taste and pocketbook. This cedar wrapped little guy is one of benchmarks for perfectly consistent, mild-mellow smooth tastings cigars. The signature blend of Dominican fillers and binder encased in in a blond USA Grown Connecticut wrapper yields one of the most enjoyable flavors that has endured for decades. If youve had them, you know. If you havent, I envy you! Origin - Dominican Republic Filler - Dominican Binder - Dominican Wrapper Type - USA Connecticut Shade

There’s a few reasons why 90 rated Ashtons have remained in the top ten for decades. They are made by the folks at Arturo Fuente. They are insanely consistent and remain one of the benchmarks for mild to mellow taste. If you’ve smoked them you know. If you haven’t, I envy you! The Symmetry edition was Ashton's first venture into adding Nicaraguan leaves with their traditional Dominican filler. The result has been several 94 ratings along with two placements in the top 25 category. This cigar was a real achievement. Not only did it offer a more complex robust taste, it retained Ashton's classic smoothness with a medium bodied flavor.

“Liga Privada” means “private blend.” It is the perfect name, as this cigar was originally crafted not for resale, but for the personal humidors of those who made them. Dozens of intricate blends were created, but No. 9 was flawless in both flavor and character. Rich, complex and full bodied without being harsh, this amazing vitola is best described in one word: satisfying.
Liga Privada No. 9 is aged a full year, no expense has been spared or shortcut taken in its creation. These cigars have a lush, earthy and espresso-like taste with incredibly dense body.

Each one was created to be perfect in flavor and aroma. Most samples are dismissed with only a rare, select few being deemed worthy, but regretfully due to tobacco limitations, costs, and construction limitations, most of these blends cannot be made into their own stand-alone line.

The Liga Privada T52 is meticulously blended over a period of two years to be a worthy humidor companion to the much heralded Liga Privada No. 9 recipe. With notes of black pepper and spice, it is a great choice when desiring a stronger, more robust smoke. Each cigar is guaranteed to be flawless in construction, flavor and character…without exception.

Literally everyone knows the name. What most folks dont know is that Macanudo was originally the name of a brand style made in Guatemala by the makers of the Punch Cuban cigars . In 1971, General Cigar, which had acquired rights to the name outside of Cuba, introduced Macanudo as a stand alone brand and the rest is cigar history! It was originally made on the Island of Jamaica under the supervision of Master Blender, Ramón Cifuentes, a veteran of Cuban cigar maker Partagas. Production shifted from Jamaica to the Dominican Republic in October 2000 where it remains. Its hard to believe that a handmade product can remain so well made and impeccably consistent for almost 50 years. The proprietary, selected blend of these cigars is a benchmark for the overused term, mild. Yes, theyre mild but also have a smooth and crispy character that has been universally accepted by millions of smokers. Over the years I have recommended the 8 count box of Glass Tubed Crystal Cafes more times than I can remember. The Henry Clay Stalk Cut series  is a blending accomplishment. The long fillers and binder contained in these box pressed vitolas are from 2012-2013 vintage crops. That alone makes for a great cigar. Where this cigar separates itself from virtually all premiums is the USA Connecticut grown Broadleaf wrapper and the harvesting method employed for this edition. We know that after leaves are cut from the plant they’re either stored, aged, cured, fermented or a combination thereof. The plants grown for this cigar wrapper are actually cut off at the stalks base. Then the entire plant is hung upside down in the curing barns to age. This process allows all the minerals, nutrients and oils to continue flowing into the leaves. The result is a totally unique tasting, smooth and balanced medium to full bodied highly rated cigar that became a top 25 cigar of the year in 2017. 

Wrapper: Connecticut Broadleaf (2012)
Binder: Dominican Piloto (2010)
Filler: Dominican Olor (2012), Piloto (2012) & Nicaragua Criollo

When this Cuban brand was launched in 1935, the world of Premium Cigars changed forever. Their #2 Torpedo became the world’s biggest selling cigar. It was here where he planted what is known as his Pilotico seeds. As time passed he also gained a reputation for establishing many growing techniques and grading guidelines that still exist today in the industry. The master blenders of Montecristo decided to pay homage to Mendez and his seeds by creating this three country blend that yields a sweet kind of medium bodied taste. The Padrón 1964 Anniversary Series line was introduced  in 1994 to commemorate the company’s 30th anniversary.  This line consists of sixteen sizes all available in sun-grown natural and maduro wrappers.

All tobacco used in this limited production series is aged for four years, creating a smooth and complex flavor. In honor of the age-old Cuban tradition of box-pressing cigars, the 1964 Anniversary line was introduced  as a box-pressed series. All these cigars are produced with a specially designed double band featuring an individually numbered guarantee label.

The Padrón 1964 Anniversary Series is consistently ranked by industry experts as one of the top brands in the world. 

Wrapper, Binder and Filler are Nicaraguan

Founded in 1964 and evolving throughout their history, the Original Padrón Series today consists of fifteen medium- to full-bodied, long-filler cigars ranging from the Cortico to the large size Magnum in both natural and maduro wrappers. A beautifully balanced cigar of exceptional quality and value, the Original Padrón line is aged for a minimum of two-and-one-half years. As with all of Padrons exceptional  offerings, this line is hand crafted using only sun-grown tobacco.

Wrapper,Binder and Filler are Nicaraguan

Davidoff Signature are the indisputable originals of the cigar world.
Timeless and elegant classics in every sense, the mild Signature blend allows fresh floral scents to mingle with earthy, woody notes, revealing a hint of sweetness that leaves a characteristically clean and creamy aftertaste. Having stood the test of time the Signature blend represents the very essence of time beautifully filled.

The Signature line pairs perfectly with elegant beverages such as Champagne where both the cigar and the beverage go hand in hand. Even with a peat and smoky Whisky the Davidoff Signature accompanies it well without being too dominant.

The Davidoff Aniversario line is made up of a great array of medium blends with flavors of cedar and spice gently unfurling into an irresistibly creamy aftertaste or warm notes of leather, nuts, black pepper and spices. All are carefully balanced and produce an exquisite aroma and  perfect draw.

Erik Espinosa is a master blender who realizes his cigars can be better and isn’t afraid to make what he feels are improvements. First off, we all need to know that AJ Fernandez is one of the true Grand Masters of cigar making. As you search our site you’ll notice major brands like H. Upmann, Monte Cristo and Romeo y Julieta have commissioned him to produce his signature blends for their cigars. Ramon Allones is still being produced in Cuba. When you consider the vast array of entries this iconic company offers, it can become pleasantly difficult deciphering what sets each one apart from another. This Miami Reserva edition stands out in that what’s known as Medio Tiempo leaves are added to the fillers. The result is a smooth and balanced medium to full bodied stick that slowly increases in intensity as you move along with a pleasant sweetness that's not overpowering.  The Havana seed line is produced at Tabacalera AJ Fernandez Cigars de Nicaragua S.A.

Now I know youre really looking for a unique cigar! Brought to us from JC Newman, the Cuesta Rey line has been around forever. The wrapper is grown on Olivas Ecuadorian farm. The cigars are then aged in Spanish Cedar lined cabinets. The result is a stick with a medium to full bodied taste as rich as its heritage. I have felt this cigar has been one of the best kept “secrets” in the business. When Davidoff first introduced this brand back in the late 90’s the “rumors” were that they were White Label “seconds”. Those of you unfamiliar with the perfectly made Davidoff White Label series need to know that this coveted line is considered the Bentley of Cigars! As retailers, we were told any White Label sticks produced that weren’t perfect in every way were put into nondescript tubes and packaging without bands and then sold in nine-count bundles. I remember first smoking one and not being able to tell the difference between its $15.00 White Label counterpart! I’ve recommended and sold a zillion of these amazing cigars over many years. The Kudzu gains noticeable strength and intensity as it moves along to a robust finish.

The box-pressed Dias De Gloria Nicaraguan Puro is perfectly made as you’d expect , draws well and burns perfectly. From it’s crisp start to the long, smooth finish, flavor notes of chocolate, caramel toffee, hardwoods, espresso and gentle spices will delight your palate without becoming overpowering even towards the end.

The dark and oily wrapped Curivari El Gran Rey is another wonderful entry from this terrific company. While it clearly is a  full bodied smoke with heaps of natural tobacco flavors, there's a great balance of sweetness and spice. Possessing Curivari's signature smoothness, this edition is a great step up for those smokers who  prefer medium bodied cigars and would like to gently up their game. One of the uncanny characteristics I've found in all the Curivaris I've smoked including this one, is their ability to keep strength and intensity under control from start to finish.
The Gloria de Leon Gran Domino blend possesses all the overall characteristics of the original in a medium to full bodied cigar.

The Curivari Gloria De Leon has attracted smokers looking  for cigar with a strictly medium body that explodes with flavor. From the minute its lit up down to its nub, the Gloria de Leon remains consistently smooth with a complex array of tastes. Think espresso, fruit, milk chocolate and bountiful spices at the very least. What makes this cigar so unique is how its strength and intensity are not overpowering while all of the flavor notes are highly amplified.

The Curivari Reserva Limitada Classica edition is a true testament to genuine craftsmanship. This cigar never gets above medium bodied insofar as strength. Where it does exceed is in the amazingly complex flavor department. It's one of the few cigars possessing a Cuban style character with a natural tobacco sweetness yielding pleasant notes of spices, cedar wood and coffee. As robust as this cigar is, it's slow burning, smooth and mellow to the finish.
All Curivari Samplers are available based on current supplies.
The Casa Turrent Origins series is produced in four different blends: Cuba, Miami, Nicaragua and San Andres. Each edition comes in the same  5 ½” by 54 sized cigar.

Guardian of the Farm is the second collaboration between Warped Cigar's Kyle Gellis and Max Fernandez from tobacco giant AGANORSA. This dark, medium to full bodied Nicaraguan puro is formally known as the Night Watch edition.

The Curivari Centauro is another great cigar coming in at the medium bodied flavor range with a heightened natural tobacco sweetness from start to finish yielding notes of cedar wood and spices.

Notes of baking spices, latte and heaps of natural tobacco flavor stay with it from start to finish. This edition was introduced in 2017 and made by the folks at Plasencia Cigars.

This edition's slightly altered blend yields all the components smokers have relished in the original along with yielding an interesting touch of sweetness. Most feel it stays within the medium bodied range throughout as opposed to increasing in intensity along the way.

The Curivari Seleccion Privada Coronations are a newer line addition of the original Seleccion Privada line. The Coronations possess a more full bodied profile with the use of a Nicaraguan Corojo wrapper vs. a Criollo that is used on the Original.

What do you get when you encase the unduplicated blend of the original Buenaventura cigar with a silky, dark and oily San Andreas Mexican wrapper? An even more complex and flavorful cigar! Yielding notes of graham cracker crust, milk chocolate and nuts along with some robust natural tobacco flavors, this solid medium bodied smoke with a wide open draw increases in strength towards the finish but remains smooth throughout.

narrative: Coming to market a year after the original Achilles, this newer blend replaced the Nicaraguan wrapper with a Mexican San Andrés  darker leaf, but kept the same Nicaraguan binder and filler tobaccos. When lit, an array of aromas from the plumes of smoke are a joy to behold even before you begin smoking it! This cigar is jammed packed with tobacco possessing an exceptional draw and slow burn. While it may start out uncommonly mild, as you make your way along, the strength and intensity increase but stay at the medium level yielding notes of honey, cocoa, dark coffee beans and natural tobacco.

The  Achilles Invensibles is noticeably higher in price and probably the company's most robust full bodied edition compared to other Achilles blends. While it does possess notes of cedar, cocoa, spicy black pepper and natural tobacco sweetness, this cigar was created for seasoned smokers who enjoy strong cigars.
Fratello Fresh Pack samplers contain a variety of the company's popular cigars. As with all products of this kind, the selections are based on in-stock availability.

Grand Cru possesses a depth and character second to none. Each individual cigar is finely crafted from meticulously selected components to deliver a layered and enchanting mild to medium-bodied experience. Carefully selected leaves create a woody, nutty and slightly spicy blend that emits a refined, woody aroma with peppery flavours.

The Davidoff 702 Series is a testament to the incredible talents of this company's Master Blenders for creating a unique hybrid tobacco seed from three original Cuban strains. Depending on the size you choose, you'll be rewarded with a seemingly endless array of flavors ranging from mild to richly robust taste. Think buttered bread,cedar wood, hot cocoa and cinnamon for starters. I'm sure you'll discover some of your own as well.

Wrapper:Ecuador - Habano 702       Binder:Dominican        Filler:Dominican

To inherit the title of Davidoff Royal Release, the journey from seed to cigar takes 10 years. Harvested separately from other crops, and cured in the Royal Barn. The Head Master Blender ensures that color, texture, aromas and later burn, are all monitored to ensure the standards demanded of a Royal are met. Bales given the Royal stamp are then left for 8 years of aging so they age to perfection. Throughout this time, they’re lavished with ideal temperature, light and humidity needed to create a cigar of such regal elegance. Everything about a Davidoff Royal Release is handpicked, including the hands that roll them. 8 of the company's  finest rollers were given the task of using their combined skill and knowledge in crafting and creating a Davidoff cigar the like of which no one has seen, held or tasted before. The Aromatica Dominicana wrapper has been chosen especially for its extraordinary beauty and shine. A wrapper specially reserved for the Royal Release line only, and won’t appear on any other Davidoff Cigar. The cigar delights the palate from the first puff with elegantly smooth flavors of oak wood, leather and fresh spices, along with notes of sweet corn and milk chocolate with a creamy aftertaste.

Davidoff has taken some of its best-selling cigars and has placed them in beautiful gift boxes. Experience rejuvenated selections for the contemporary cigar enthusiast. Exclusively available in the United States.

These premium selections embody an experience of flavors and aromas that Davidoff is known for. Created for the aficionado searching for a wide variety of beautiful, premium quality cigars, this assortment is available in both a 9 and 12 count box.

Davidoff Small Batch Cigars are a series of limited edition cigars made with different blends and only available in very limited numbered quantities. Each one is packaged in paper bundles of five or ten cigars.

The Timeless Panamericana line is a unique medium plus to full-bodied cigars blended of Central American tobaccos available in 4 sizes of 10 count boxes. Each offering is highly rated. These expertly made cigars are produced at Plasencia Cigars S.A. in Estelí, Nicaragua with an Ecuadorian Sumatra wrapper over a Nicaraguan binder and fillers from Costa Rica and Nicaragua.

The Dunbarton Mi Querida Triqui Traca blend is a very rich and complex tasting cigar that's just a bit stronger than the original version . With just the right amount of peppery spice to keep things zesty, this medium to full bodied flavor bomb yields heaps of robust aromatic smoke. While this cigar's strength and intensity increase along the way, the overall character never gets overpowering.

Wrapper: U.S.A. (Connecticut Broadleaf) Number 1 Dark Corona grade
Binder: Nicaragua
Filler: Nicaragua & Dominican Republic

The Sobremesa Brûlée is unlike any of the company's other editions. When this blend was introduced, Dunbarton founder Steve Saka said, “Sobremesa Brûlée is a recreation of the milder, shade wrapped ligas of my early years.” The Brûlée is not supposed to be like the amped-up Connie’s (Connecticut's) we’ve seen in the market over the last few years. Instead, it’s a throwback to your “grandfather’s Connecticut.” With that said, what smokers should know is this cigar's overall flavor is medium to full leveled with a medium body. The strength is quite mild which makes for an enjoyable smoke any time of the day. All sizes are produced in 13 count boxes.

Wrapper: Ecuador (Connecticut)
Binder: Mexico (Matacapan negro de Temporal)
Filler: Nicaragua (Condega C-SG, Pueblo Nuevo Criollo, Estelí C-98 & Estelí Hybrid Ligero)

I know you’re probably wondering why I would give a machine made, short filler, domestic cigar such a high rating. After all, I’m a handmade Premium guy. Every now and again, a product comes along that serves its purpose and completes its mission. When J.C. Newman created this brand’s first Classic “Kickin” bagged and jarred editions many years ago, it took awhile to get noticed. As they found their way into humidors across the country, curiosity got the better of many folks that opened the containers and took a sniff. And that was that! The intoxicating aroma these sticks gave off led to a try which then led to buying the whole container. Without getting too involved, each edition is mellow to slightly medium bodied. They’re all infused resulting in a smooth, sweet, rum like flavor that’s thoroughly enjoyable any time of the day. They keep fresh in their containers and have a totally guilt free price offering any smoker a great diversion. Origin - United States Filler - Dominican-Honduran-Nicaraguan Binder - Coming Soon! Introduced in 2014, this wild looking figurado-torpedo hybrid 6.25 x 54 sized cigar's exact contents are “Undisclosed”. The award-winning Padrón 1926 Serie premiered in 2002 to commemorate José O. Padrón’s 75th birthday, with ten sizes available. Continuing our tradition, this series is offered in a box-pressed format. These cigars are individually handcrafted from tobacco aged five years, then blended to create an exceptionally smooth, complex, balanced and full-bodied flavor. For protection, a double band with an individually numbered guarantee label is applied to every cigar to safeguard against counterfeiting. Available in both sun-grown natural and maduro wrappers.

Filler - Nicaraguan / Binder - Nicaraguan / Wrapper  - Nicaraguan

The Padrón 1964 Anniversary Series line was introduced  in 1994 to commemorate the company’s 30th anniversary.  This line consists of sixteen sizes all available in sun-grown natural and maduro wrappers.

All tobacco used in this limited production series is aged for four years, creating a smooth and complex flavor. In honor of the age-old Cuban tradition of box-pressing cigars, the 1964 Anniversary line was introduced  as a box-pressed series. All these cigars are produced with a specially designed double band featuring an individually numbered guarantee label.

The Padrón 1964 Anniversary Series is consistently ranked by industry experts as one of the top brands in the world.

Wrapper, Binder and Filler are Nicaraguan

Founded in 1964 and evolving throughout their history, the Original Padrón Series today consists of fifteen medium- to full-bodied, long-filler cigars ranging from the Cortico to the large size Magnum in both natural and maduro wrappers. A beautifully balanced and full-bodied smoke of exceptional quality and value, the Original Padrón line is aged for a minimum of two-and-one-half years. As with all of our exceptional cigar offerings, this line is hand crafted using only sun-grown tobacco.

Wrapper,Binder and Filler are Nicaraguan

The Don Lino Africa line was launched in 2004 and has steadily gained popularity over the years. Produced by Master Blender A.J. Fernandez, these highly rated, medium to full bodied squarely box pressed cigars are slow burning and flavorful.

The artisans at Cohiba present, Royale, the epitome of luxury, an experience for those with extravagant tastes who only demand the finest. For this cigar, the craftsmen begin with the finest Nicaraguan broadleaf wrapper. It’s rich, oily, and pure perfection. Next, the Nicaraguan wrapper is meticulously blended with full-bodied and sophisticated Nicaraguan, Dominican, and Honduran tobaccos. Finally, it’s all brought together by the binder, an exquisite Piloto Cubano tobacco that culminates in the most finely-tuned smoking experience Cohiba has ever created. The Gran Royale is a top pick!

Binder: Dominican Piloto Cubano

Nick Perdomo and his Dad are well renowned cigar makers. I’ve watched them grow to one of the world’s powerhouse teams producing a wide array of highly rated premiums. In fact, over 20 years ago I remember Nick personally traveling around the country and winding up in my Long Island store soliciting for business! Many years later when I went to the last big Cigar Show trying to see him was like trying to see a rock start! His success is well earned. When this 10th Anniversary Champagne line was launched it was well received. Let’s face it, Perdomo only makes great cigars! This editions Nicaraguan sun grown wrapper encasing Perdomos vintage Nicaraguan leaves yields a medium to full bodied, spicy flavor. Justin Andrews, senior brand manager at General Cigar Co. recently described this particular cigar in a press release as follows, “With Estelí Puro, we made a collection that is completely unique in its bold flavor profile, yet has many of the attributes that have made the other Diesel expressions a cigar of choice among dyed-in-the-wool smokers. This is a cigar that demands the smoker’s full attention with deep and balanced flavor, a strong presentation and an attractive price point.”
While we may think differently about pricing, I agree with him about this medium to more than full bodied cigar getting your attention after you light up. Peppery spice begins immediately but somewhat fades as the rest of the cigar's attributes increase in strength and intensity along the way. Think ground coffee beans, citrus and hazelnuts for starters but the star of the show is the ever rising robustness and strength of this cigar's natural tobacco flavor. The highly critical folks at Blind Man's Puff rated the robusto a 93!

Wrapper: Nicaraguan (La Lilia)
Binder: Nicaraguan (San José)
Filler: Nicaraguan (San Lotano)

What do you get when you triple ferment the Sun Grown wrapper from the original Curivari Sun Grown edition?  A Maduro Sun Grown wrapper. What do you get when you encase the inner blend with this dark oily wrapper? Everything the original has with a noticeable increase in strength and intensity. So if you're a fan of the unique flavor characteristics of the Sun Grown, this Maduro will give you the same earthy notes of leather, grass, hay and pepper in a more full bodied, robust and slightly sweeter smoke.

narrative: Foundation owner Nick Melillo traveled to the island of Jamaica in 2015 to have some fun along with searching for the country’s rarely used tobacco. He soon located one of the oldest farms growing and processing leaves utilizing traditional methods that have been employed for over a thousand years. He then put his mad scientist hat on and combined his Master Blender skills by applying what he calls “Caribbean atmospheric herbal fusion” creating the Upsetter line. The short version  is that the combination of this process with coveted Jamaican and vintage Nicaraguan leaves produced a series of cigars ranging from mild and smooth to medium-full bodied and beyond. Yes, they’re totally different and have become pleasant diversions for experienced smokers as well as newcomers.

Offering cigar aficionados the quintessential range of flavors, The [Diamond] Zaya Collection is blended from a selection of the highest quality tobaccos, blended with 15 year aged tobacco. The perfection of this Collection lies in the

Known for its wide range of different sizes and blends, The Luxus Collection consists of ten tobacco lines aged for 10 years, and matured for a year or less. This Collection includes some of El Septimo’s best-sellers and the world’s most-known brands, because come, on… have you ever seen cigars like these before?! Cigars range from 2-inch 20-minute smokes, to tiny Torpedos and even baby cigarillos. But, one thing remains the same: All of the cigars part of the line possess refined aromas, velvety smokes, and are known for their oily and supple dark wrappers. Draws are full & generous with easy & gentle light-ups, as even the fuller-bodied lines gain savor & depth over time. In short, these are sportier cigars for experienced enthusiasts!

Now the world can smoke an El Septimo Cigar designed and dedicated for each day of the week. The Alexandra Collection of Cigars were originally designed and blended exclusively for women after intensive market research, testing, & blending techniques, fitting women’s preferences in regards to flavor, size, strength, smoothness, aroma, & combustion. The Collection offers light to mild products, as the lightest leaf from each vintage is chosen. This blend offers an experience that changes flavors, ranging from woody & intense with a distinct oak & tea blend, to a mild caramel sweetness with a pleasing, but not overpowering, aroma. Although exclusively designed for women, the Alexandras can be enjoyed by all who are passionate for fine tasting mild cigars.

The Gilgamesh Collection is El Septimo’s latest addition, and offers the first 50 gauge cigars part of the brand. Symbolizing one of the oldest stories written into existence based on the historical records of Assyrian King Gilgamesh, this collection provides a unique tasting experience while focusing on the strength, flavor, aroma, and combustion of the cigar. Offering both medium bodied and full bodied cigars, these cigars’ burns last for a long period of time, while possessing a milder light-up than the traditional El Septimo Cigar, resulting in a gradual pace with the perfect balance between thickness and length.

Introduced in December of 2021 and made by famed Aganorsa Leaf, this medium to full bodied cigar utilizes a rare twin binder of 2012 Corojo leaf along with a vintage Nicaraguan wrapper and filler leaves. Being named the #9 cigar of 2021 by the discerning folks at Cigar Dojo got it off to a good start.

Wrapper: Nicaragua
Binder: Nicaragua (Corojo 2012)
Filler: Nicaragua

The Aganorsa Aniversario Maduro blend includes a Nicaraguan shade-grown dark maduro wrapper encasing select Nicaraguan tobacco used in both the binder and filler. This fairly strong cigar retains a unique smoothness throughout making it balanced, flavorful and very complex tasting.  This perfectly made cigar has a great draw yielding aromatic and spicy smoke.

Wrapper: Nicaragua (Corojo Maduro)     Binder: Nicaragua          Filler: Nicaragua

The Oscar McFly is a complexly blended medium to full flavored cigar with notes of cedar wood, roasted nuts, coffee beans and natural tobacco sweetness with just a touch of spice. Both overall body and strength range from medium to medium plus. The construction and draw are outstanding on all three sizes. The Toro is a top pick.

Wrapper: San Andreas Mexico
Binder: Honduras
Filler: Dominican Republic, Honduras & Nicaragua

Oddly enough, the Caldwell Blind Man’s Bluff Nicaraguan puro is made at Scandinavian Tobacco Groups Honduran factory, the makers of Partagás, Punch, Hoyo de Monterrey, Cohiba, La Gloria Cubana, Don Tomás and CAO. This medium bodied edition features an oily toothy Nicaraguan Habano wrapper encasing selected Nicaraguan leaves and is available in three popular sizes.

WRAPPER:Nicaraguan Habano
BINDER:Nicaraguan
FILLER:Nicaragua

The Dunbarton Stillwell Star line represents the most amazing blending achievement combining vintage cigar leaves with the highest grades of premium pipe tobaccos with Ecuadorian Habano wrappers and Mexican San Andrés Negro binders. All styles are produced in 13 count boxes. 

Each offerings fillers are complex and unique. The Dunbarton Company describes them as follows,
- Aromatic No. 1 — The finest of aromatic Black Cavendish, Golden Virginia and Burley pipe tobaccos added to a mild, Nicaraguan puro to provide a delightfully smooth and room-pleasing smoking experience. Each cigar is delicately finished with a cabeza dulce.
- English No. 27 — A quintessential mix of Burley and Turkish leaf with a generous portion of Cypriot Latakia pressed cake paired with Nicaraguan cigar tobaccos. Rich and decadent, this is a Latakia-lover’s puro worthy of being smoked in an English Manor House.
- Bayou No. 32 — A combination of Bright and Red Virginia leaf with the most select St. James Parish Perique pipe tobacco added to a medium-bodied Nicaraguan puro. It rewards the smoker with a classic yet entrancing, any time of the day relaxing experience.
- Navy No. 1056 — A crumble cake of stoved Red and Golden Virginias with a touch of “Naval Rations” combined with Orientals and Latakia expertly blended with dark air cured black cigar leaf, this puro rewards the smoker with a unique, aromatic indulgence.

The Drew Estate Florida Sungrown 20 Acre Farm line blend covers the entire spectrum of body and strength. While it starts off mild, it gradually moves to medium and tips slightly into the full bodied range at the finish. From the beginning, these well made, cedar wrapped cigars are sweet, creamy, complexly flavored and balanced. The Robusto and Toro are top picks

Wrapper: Ecuador (Shade Grown Connecticut)
Binder: Honduras (Habano)
Filler: Nicaragua (Estelí & Jalapa) & U.S.A. (Florida Sun Grown)

The Crowned Heads Le Patissier Corona Gorda was originally introduced as a 2021 PCA  Exclusive offering. Considering this cigars overall strength, it never seems to get overpowering.

Filler: Costa Rica & Nicaragua (Ometepe, Pueblo Nuevo)

La FLor Dominicana Bundles are medium to slightly full bodied 5x42  corona sized cigars are produced is three varieties: Connecticut, Habano and Sumatran. These value priced entries are offered based on availability.

The mild to medium bodied Timeless Sterling collection was originally introduced in 2013. It combines Dominican fillers and binder tobaccos with a gorgeous Ecuador-grown Connecticut wrapper producing rich, silky body and balanced strength and aromas.The cigars are available in five sizes – each presented in ten-count boxes.

The Illusione ESP is a 4 x 52 Robusto that consists entirely of selected, vintage Nicaraguan tobaccos from the Aganorsa Leaf farm including very rare Corojo 2006 viso leaves in the filler. This limited edition cigar's production totals 1,500 boxes of 10 cigars.

The DBL Mafu is a very powerful cigar that is balanced, complex and packed with plenty of flavor. Mafu is offered in two wrappers, A Mexican San Andres Maduro and an Ecuadorian Cameroon. Both offerings have the same binder, Havana Vuelta Abajo (HVA) and filler blend of Dominican- grown Corojo 99 and Pennsylvania Broadleaf. These cigars are available in two sizes, the Gordo (8 x 60) or a box-pressed toro (6 x 54) packaged in 30-count boxes containing 15 maduro and 15 Cameroon in each box. The highly critical folks at Stogie Press gave the DBL Mafu a 90 rating.

The Stolen Throne 3 Kingdoms is made at the Flor de San Luis factory in Esteli, Nicaragua. These flawlessly made medium to full bodied box pressed cigars yield deep and rich flavors of naturally sweet tobacco taste and hints of spices.

WRAPPER:Nicaragua Habano Oscuro
BINDER:Nicaragua
FILLER:Nicaragua

The Stolen Throne Call to Arms was released in the Summer of 2020. Lee Marsh purposely blended this to be unique from their initial release, the Crook of the Crown. These medium to full bodied cigars are expertly made with an old school semi-closed foot. Yielding heaps of aromatic smoke from a wide open draw, the Call to Arms are flavor bombs offering an array of taste notes with a super smooth delivery from start to finish.

WRAPPER:Sumatra
BINDER:Nicaraguan
FILLER:Nicaraguan

The Stolen Crown Crook of the Crown is the company's inaugural cigar. This well made, complexly blended vitola utilizes a a 10-year old San Andres maduro wrapper with fillers from Indonesia and Nicaragua along with an Indonesian binder ending in a closed foot. These exceptionally smooth smoking cigars stay squarely in the medium bodied strength range from start to finish. Along the way an array of flavor notes and peppery spices combine with natural tobacco taste and aromatic smoke. The highly critical folks at Blind Man's Puff rated the Robusto at 94!

Fernandez is a smooth smoking mixture of naturally sweet tobacco flavors combined with a variety of taste notes that are very enjoyable. All three sizes are produced in 10 count boxes.

The Host line is one of the best-selling premium cigar experiences on the American market. Made at Davidoff’s famous Diadema Cigars de Honduras SA cigar factory, this hugely popular line features finely aged Honduran  binder and filler tobaccos at their heart and encased in a top-quality Connecticut Shade wrapper. These smooth, mellow and naturally sweet cigars have been a favorite for countless smokers for decades.

The Host Maduro line employs the same filler and binder leaves used in its Connecticut wrapped counterpart. The difference is the dark and oily Connecticut Broadleaf wrapper. This features gives these cigars more of a medium body while retaining the Host brands signature smoothness.

The Metropolitan Connecticut edition uses a Connecticut shade wrapper over a Dominican binder and Dominican fillers. This blend has long been considered a traditional expression of a what a smooth and mellow Dominican cigar with a Connecticut wrapper should be.

The Metropolitan Habano edition was released in 2016. Made at Plasencia Cigars S.A. in Estelí, Nicaragua, this Nicaraguan puro was a sharp departure from the brands other two blends.  Virtually all sizes were highly rated extolling the smooth, rich and satisfying flavor of this medium plus to slightly full flavored cigar.

Maintaining the core tenants of the brand, the H99 features a Corojo leaves from the heart of the Connecticut River Valley along with  San Andres Otapan  over a core blend of well-aged Nicaraguan and Honduran tripa leaf. The marked contrast between naturally sweet tobacco spice with dense earthy layers produces a luxuriously rich smoke that fully reveals itself in an epic finish.

The medium to full bodied All Saints St. Francis is the third  offering from this great small batch, boutique company.
